Classifying includes looking at a user input and a given a set of criteria, including a list of possible skills and entities, and determining if any of the skills are sufficient to match the input. Multiple skills can be returned, if applicable. If a skill is deemed to be a good match, then attributes associated with that skill should be reviewed to see if the input contains any attribute information as defined in the criteria. Not all skills have attributes associated with them. When looking at attributes, you may see some “Possible values”. These represent the only values that could be returned for that attribute. 
Regarding the format for your response, it should be a YAML. For any skill returned, all corresponding attributes should also be returned with values as found in the user input. If no attribute value is found, populate the attribute value field with “None found”. When constructing your YAML, return only the identifier for both the skills and attributes, along with the attribute values.
- intent_id1:
   slot_id1: slot1_value
   slot_id2: slot2_value
- intent_id2:
   slot_id1: slot1_value
   slot_id2: slot2_value
